review.body:
I increased the size to 10045; 10045 is the size corresponding to SSL_CURVE_P256_FRODO640AES

I'm not sure I understand: Where did you do this increase and how did you compute it? And why did you choose that algorithm and not the other (BIKE) hybrid?

Last question: There is an interop test with the interop test server at test.openquantumsafe.org in the oqs-scripts directory that for some reason is not part of CI. Did you run this as part of your testing (and does it pass)?

review.body:
Thanks for this contribution. 

This PR removes the data needed to generate historical algorithm IDs (in https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl/blob/OQS-OpenSSL_1_1_1-stable/oqs-template/oqs-kem-info.md and https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl/blob/OQS-OpenSSL_1_1_1-stable/oqs-template/oqs-sig-info.md). 

As we're stopping maintenance of oqs-openssl111 (and don't update those files already) that's surely no problem, but if those files are referenced anywhere, it would be good to replace them as part of our "decommissioning" with links to the still maintained versions at https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-provider/blob/main/oqs-template/oqs-kem-info.md and https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-provider/blob/main/oqs-template/oqs-sig-info.md --> Suggestion to @dstebila to replace these two files with pointers to the `oqs-provider` replacements when adding the "discontinuation" notice to this project after its final release -- or maybe already now in this PR.

##### Checklist

- [ x] documentation is added or updated
- [ x] tests are added or updated

Fixes to oqs-template/generate.yml that were causing "nist-security levels not found" errors in oqs-template/generate.py. Certain default algorithms included in the file are no longer valid for liboqs builds that use the latest verison. 

The following algorithms were removed:

- Kyber90s variants
- SPHINCS+ Haraka variants
- SPHINCS+ robust variants
- Dilithium AES variants
